Kannywood actress Sadiya Haruna has been sentenced to six-month imprisonment without an option of a fine by a Magistrate Court sitting at Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport in Kano. The Court, presided over by Justice Muntari Garba Dandago sentenced the Kannywood star for defamation and slandering of actor Isa A. Isa. In a viral video, she accused her colleague of being a homosexual, bastard and an unrepentant womaniser. She also alleged that he requested anal sex from her and posted videos of him on social media while she continued to accuse him of several despicable acts. Isa denied all the allegations against him and sued Sadiya for character assassination.   Afghanistan receives $32m in humanitarian cash aid     Ronke Odusanyaâ€™s baby Daddy apologises for DNA request     Uche Ogbodo confirms secret marriage to baby daddy   - Advertisement - She was sentenced by Justice Muntari Garba Dandago who threatened the jail term will be extended to three years if she continues to defame Isa. He however noted she had three months to appeal the judgement. In 2021, Sadiya was arrested by Hisbah and convicted by a Sharia Court for obscenity and indecent acts after sharing sexual content on her social media pages. Haruna pleaded guilty to a one-count charge of obscenity and indecent act, which contradicts section 355 of Penal Code Law 2000. Sentencing her, the presiding judge, Justice Ali Jibril Danzaki ordered she attended a Darul Hadith Islamiyya session at Tudun Yola Quarters for a period of six months.